target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613120\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fue1665702580943.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fue1665702580943.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fue1665702580943.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fue1665702580943\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Contained Form\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A contained form is a secondary, non-modal window that is displayed in a form container widget, or as a tab in a tab widget. It is defined by setting the window property <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Contained</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fue1665702580943__section_szb_qcx_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d125712e57\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fue1665702580943__p_d100193e1_d100194e1_d100195e1\">When <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span> is set to\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Contained</code>, the following properties are automatically set, and cannot be\n        modified:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__1\"> Property </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__2\"> Value </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Caption</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Resizable</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Modality &amp; Attachment</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Non-modal, Attached</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Independant Form</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fue1665702580943__table_d11690e1_d11691e1_d11692e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"fue1665702580943__note_m2c_rcx_swb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> A contained form with split bars should have a layout\n        that fits the widget, otherwise the runtime form instance may be larger than the limits\n        defined by the split bars. For example, don't make the contained form fit in a portrait Tab\n        widget and later use it in a landscape Form Container. Uniface does not store the layout of\n        split bars when they are placed on a contained form.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gev1665702640020.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ucontainer (FormContainer)</a><p>The ucontainer widget embeds a non-modal form in a field of the current form. Uniface provides a logical widget called FormContainer, which is mapped to ucontainer.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzj1665702641924.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>utab (Tab)</a><p>The utab widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tab, which is mapped to utab.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyf1688451219719.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>utabex (TabEx)</a><p>The utabex widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. The utabex widget is highly customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. Uniface provides a logical widget called TabEx, which is mapped to utabex.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613120\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613120\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Contained Form Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Contained Form A contained form is a secondary, non-modal window that is displayed in a form container widget, or as a tab in a tab widget. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Contained . Description When Window Type is set to Contained , the following properties are automatically set, and cannot be modified: Property Value Caption False Resizable False Modality & Attachment Non-modal, Attached Is Independant Form False Note: A contained form with split bars should have a layout that fits the widget, otherwise the runtime form instance may be larger than the limits defined by the split bars. For example, don't make the contained form fit in a portrait Tab widget and later use it in a landscape Form Container. Uniface does not store the layout of split bars when they are placed on a contained form. Related Links ucontainer (FormContainer) The ucontainer widget embeds a non-modal form in a field of the current form. Uniface provides a logical widget called FormContainer, which is mapped to ucontainer. utab (Tab) The utab widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tab, which is mapped to utab. utabex (TabEx) The utabex widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. The utabex widget is highly customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. Uniface provides a logical widget called TabEx, which is mapped to utabex. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}